Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for Next.js App Router

Successfully installed and configured @vercel/analytics package as requested.

## Changes Made:

### 1. Installed Package
- Added @vercel/analytics package using npm
- Package version: Latest (managed by npm)

### 2. Modified Files

**app/layout.tsx**
- Imported Analytics component from '@vercel/analytics/next'
- Added <Analytics /> component inside the <body> tag after {children}
- Preserved all existing code structure and functionality
- Component placement follows Vercel's recommended practice for App Router

**package.json**
- Added @vercel/analytics to dependencies

**package-lock.json**
- Updated with new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics

## Verification:

✓ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✓ TypeScript compilation passed
✓ Static pages generated without errors
✓ Linter checked (1 pre-existing error in lib/market.ts, not related to this change)
✓ No tests configured in project

## Implementation Details:

The Analytics component was added to the root layout file (app/layout.tsx) which is the correct location for App Router projects. This ensures that analytics tracking is active across all pages of the application.

The component was placed after the {children} prop inside the <body> tag, which is the recommended location according to Vercel's documentation. This allows the main content to load first while the analytics script loads asynchronously in the background.

All existing code, including:
- Font configurations (Inter and JetBrains Mono)
- Metadata settings
- Providers wrapper
- Dark mode configuration

...has been preserved without modification.
